The paper discusses an audio dataset designed for training and evaluating keyword spotting systems, which falls under the sub-category of speech recognition (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the need for a specialized dataset for this task, which involves recognizing limited vocabulary spoken words, which could fall under the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also suggests a methodology for reproducible and comparable accuracy metrics, which could fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
